{"title_page": "Best Look Lately", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=March 2019}}\n{{short description|2014 single by Dear Rouge}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Best Look Lately\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Dear Rouge]]\n| album      = [[Black to Gold]]\n| released   = April 22, 2014\n| format     = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Indie pop]], [[alternative rock]]\n| length     = 3:11\n| label      = Independent\n| writer     = Drew McTaggart, Danielle McTaggart, Adam Stewart, Brodie Tavares, Stefan Tavares, Maclean Carlson, Ryan Worsley\n| producer   = Drew McTaggart, [[Howard Redekopp]], Ryan Worsley\n| prev_title = [[I Heard I Had]]\n| prev_year  = 2013\n| next_title = Black to Gold\n| next_year  = 2015\n}}\n\n\"'''Best Look Lately'''\" is the third single from Canadian [[indie rock]] band [[Dear Rouge]]. In a press release, Drew McTaggart remarked about the song: \"We all know of our world's endless bombardment of things to better ourselves. We hope to offer a song to people that fights back at this cultural obsession, and at the same time gives you a boost of confidence. We've always found that the people who are most content are the ones we strive to be like, more than someone who is perfect!\".\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video for \"Best Look Lately\" premiered on [[MTV Canada]]'s website on November 14, 2014.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mtv.ca/music/artist/d/4091183/dear-rouge/1100176/best-look-lately |title=Archived copy |access-date=2014-11-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129114226/http://www.mtv.ca/music/artist/d/4091183/dear-rouge/1100176/best-look-lately |archive-date=2014-11-29 |url-status=dead}}</ref> The video is a fast paced time lapse of Danielle sitting and having her makeup or \"look\" changed several times. Her makeup is styled after [[Cyndi Lauper]], [[David Bowie]], [[Twiggy]] and [[Lady Gaga]] at certain points in the video. The video ends with her makeup and hair being made more natural and Drew sitting at her side as the lights turn out.\n\n==Charts==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Chart (2014)\n! Peak<br>position\n|-\n|-\n|[[Canadian Rock/Alternative chart|Canadian Alternative Rock Chart]]\n|align=\"center\"|12\n|-\n| ''Billboard'' [[Canadian rock/alternative chart|Canadian Rock Airplay]]<ref>{{cite web |last=Rock |first=Canadian |url=http://charts.bdsradio.com/bdsradiocharts/charts.aspx?formatid=37 |title=Canadian Active Rock #18; BDS |website=Bdsradio.com |date=2013-12-08 |accessdate=2013-12-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111012025806/http://charts.bdsradio.com/bdsradiocharts/charts.aspx?formatid=37 |archive-date=2011-10-12 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 25\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2014 songs]]\n[[Category:Dear Rouge songs]]\n\n\n{{2010s-rock-song-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=March 2019}}\n{{short description|2014 single by Dear Rouge}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Best Look Lately\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Dear Rouge]]\n| album      = [[Black to Gold]]\n| released   = April 22, 2014\n| format     = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Indie pop]], [[alternative rock]]\n| length     = 3:11\n| label      = Independent\n| writer     = Drew McTaggart, Danielle McTaggart, Adam Stewart, Brodie Tavares, Stefan Tavares, Maclean Carlson, Ryan Worsley\n| producer   = Drew McTaggart, [[Howard Redekopp]], Ryan Worsley\n| prev_title = [[I Heard I Had]]\n| prev_year  = 2013\n| next_title = Black to Gold\n| next_year  = 2015\n}}\n\n\"'''Best Look Lately'''\" is the third single from Canadian [[indie rock]] band [[Dear Rouge]]. In a press release, Drew McTaggart said the following about the song: \"We all know of our world's endless bombardment of things to better ourselves. We hope to offer a song to people that fights back at this cultural obsession, and at the same time gives you a boost of confidence. We've always found that the people who are most content are the ones we strive to be like, more than someone who is perfect!\".\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video for \"Best Look Lately\" premiered on [[MTV Canada]]'s website on November 14, 2014.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mtv.ca/music/artist/d/4091183/dear-rouge/1100176/best-look-lately |title=Archived copy |access-date=2014-11-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129114226/http://www.mtv.ca/music/artist/d/4091183/dear-rouge/1100176/best-look-lately |archive-date=2014-11-29 |url-status=dead}}</ref> The video is a fast paced time lapse of Danielle sitting and having her makeup or \"look\" changed several times. Her makeup is styled after [[Cyndi Lauper]], [[David Bowie]], [[Twiggy]] and [[Lady Gaga]] at certain points in the video. The video ends with her makeup and hair being made more natural and Drew sitting at her side as the lights turn out.\n\n==Charts==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Chart (2014)\n! Peak<br>position\n|-\n|-\n|[[Canadian Rock/Alternative chart|Canadian Alternative Rock Chart]]\n|align=\"center\"|12\n|-\n| ''Billboard'' [[Canadian rock/alternative chart|Canadian Rock Airplay]]<ref>{{cite web |last=Rock |first=Canadian |url=http://charts.bdsradio.com/bdsradiocharts/charts.aspx?formatid=37 |title=Canadian Active Rock #18; BDS |website=Bdsradio.com |date=2013-12-08 |accessdate=2013-12-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111012025806/http://charts.bdsradio.com/bdsradiocharts/charts.aspx?formatid=37 |archive-date=2011-10-12 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 25\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2014 songs]]\n[[Category:Dear Rouge songs]]\n\n\n{{2010s-rock-song-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ames86", "label": "safe", "comment": "slight wording change for conciseness", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/w