ike Fleming|date=2013-09-11|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> Nicolas Cage,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-ghostrider2-idUSTRE81F19720120216|title=\"Ghost Rider 2\" poised to ignite lackluster franchise|date=2012-02-16|work=Reuters|access-date=2019-07-03|language=en}}</ref> and many more.\n\nAmritraj\u2019s extraordinary career from Wimbledon tennis player to billion dollar Hollywood producer (chronicled in his autobiography Advantage Hollywood<ref>{{Cite book|title=Advantage Hollywood|last=Amritraj|first=Ashok|publisher=Harper Collins Publishers India|year=2013|isbn=978-93-5029-359-1|location=India|pages=}}</ref>) is matched only by his commitment to education, diversity, and gender equality. Dedicating a significant amount of his time to philanthropic endeavors worldwide, in 2016 Amritraj was appointed as the first United Nations India Goodwill Ambassador for the 17 UN Sustainable Development Goals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/biz/news/hyde-park-ashok-amritraj-un-india-1201974655/|title=Hyde Park Entertainment\u2019s Ashok Amritraj on His New Role as India Goodwill Ambassador|last=Frater|first=Patrick|last2=Frater|first2=Patrick|date=2017-02-02|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> In December 2018, by decree of the President of the Republic of France, Amritraj was appointed a Chevalier (Knight) of the Ordre National du Merit\u00e9.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/asia/ashok-amritraj-decorated-french-government-1203089843/|title=Ashok Amritraj Decorated by French Government|last=Frater|first=Patrick|last2=Frater|first2=Patrick|date=2018-12-14|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref>\n\nAmritraj has grown Hyde Park into a cutting-edge independent alternative to the traditional Hollywood system, fully realizing his vision for a progressive global company that incorporates the most essential elements of a full-fledged studio. Hyde Park\u2019s mandate encompasses feature film, television, digital, documentary, and local language content, with the Company possessing development, production, and financing capabilities in addition to handling worldwide sales and marketing.\n\nAmritraj has had box office hits such as GHOST RIDER: SPIRIT OF VENGEANCE, starring Nicolas Cage,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/la-xpm-2012-feb-17-la-fi-ct-projector-20120217-story.html|title=Movie Projector: 'Ghost Rider' sequel to scorch competition|date=2012-02-17|work=Los Angeles Times|access-date=2019-07-03|language=en-US|issn=0458-3035}}</ref> BRINGING DOWN THE HOUSE, starring Steve Martin,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2003/film/reviews/bringing-down-the-house-1200543214/|title=Bringing Down the House|last=McCarthy|first=Todd|last2=McCarthy|first2=Todd|date=2003-02-23|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> PREMONITION, starring Sandra Bullock,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.backstage.com/magazine/article/mcmahon-premonition-tristar-31081/|title=McMahon Has 'Premonition' for TriStar|date=2005-11-10|website=www.backstage.com|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> WALKING TALL starring The Rock, and many more, as well as critically acclaimed titles including 99 HOMES starring Andrew Garfield and Michael Shannon, BLUE VALENTINE starring Ryan Gosling and Michelle Williams,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hydeparkentertainment.com/news/2019/6/5/blue-valentine-is-an-indie-film|title=Right Cinema: Blue Valentine is an Indie Film|website=Hyde Park Entertainment Group|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> and SHOPGIRL, starring Steve Martin and Claire Danes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2003/scene/markets-festivals/fox-takes-international-on-hyde-park-shopgirl-1117892612/|title=Fox takes international on Hyde Park \u2018Shopgirl\u2019|last=Brodesser|first=Cathy Dunkley,Claude|last2=Dunkley|first2=Cathy|date=2003-09-18|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03|last3=Brodesser|first3=Claude}}</ref>\n\nAmritraj\u2019s current projects include: supernatural thriller, PREY, in partnership with Blumhouse Productions <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/06/prey-logan-miller-blumhouse-hyde-park-1201769872/|title=Hyde Park-Image Nation & Blumhouse Partner For \u2018Prey\u2019|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|last2=D'Alessandro|first2=Anthony|date=2016-06-09|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref>, PASHMINA, a Major Animated Musical in partnership with Netflix, to be directed by Gurinder Chadha and with music by Oscar-winner A.R. Rahman <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/pashmina-gurinder-chadha-nidhi-chanani-netflix-ashok-amritraj-hyde-park-animated-musical-india-blinded-by-the-light-1202570675/|title=Netflix Teams With Gurinder Chadha & Ashok Amritraj\u2019s Hyde Park To Turn Nidhi Chanani Graphic Novel \u2018Pashmina\u2019 Into Animated Musical|last=Jr|first=Mike Fleming|last2=Jr|first2=Mike Fleming|date=2019-03-06|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> and FORDLANDIA, a Television event series, to be directed by Werner Herzog at AMC Studios <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/fordlandia-novel-adapted-tv-werner-herzog-direct-greg-grandin-hyde-park-entertainment-group-1202410725/|title=\u2018Fordlandia\u2019 Novel Being Adapted For TV; Werner Herzog To Direct|last=Petski|first=Denise|last2=Petski|first2=Denise|date=2018-06-14|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref>.\n\nHyde Park Entertainment Group and its artists have received awards and recognition from the major award shows and film festivals including the Oscars, the BAFTA awards, the Emmys, the Independent Spirit Awards, the Cannes Film Festival, the Golden Globes, and many more.\n\nAmritraj serves on the Producers Executive Board of the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiawest.com/online_features/ashok-amritraj---hollywood-film-producer/article_f071eed0-db90-11e3-b969-0019bb2963f4.html|title=ASHOK AMRITRAJ - Hollywood Film Producer|website=India West|language=en|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref> and on the advisory board for the Dodge Film School at Chapman University <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blogs.chapman.edu/dodge/2017/08/16/dodge-college-moves-up-to-6-spot-in-the-hollywood-reporters-annual-ranking-of-top-25-film-schools/|title=Dodge College Moves Up to #6 Spot in The Hollywood Reporter\u2019s Annual Ranking of Top 25 Film Schools - Maintains \u2018Top 10\u2019 Status for 5th Consecutive Year|website=Dodge College of Film and Media Arts|language=en-US|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref>. In 2015, he was bestowed an honorary Doctorate of the Arts from the University of East London <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/sports/ashok-amritraj-awarded-honorary-doctorate-by-a-london-varsity/articleshow/49842998.cms|title=Ashok Amritraj awarded honorary doctorate by a London Varsity|date=2015-11-19|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2019-07-03}}</ref>.\n\n==Early life==\nAshok lived in Chennai his mother's name is Maggie Dhairyam and father's name is Robert Amritraj. He has two brothers, [[Vijay Amritraj]] and Anand Amritraj, His brothers Vijay Amritraj,[[Anand Amritraj]] was international tennis players.\n\n==Personal life==\n\n==Filmography==\n===As Producer===\n* ''[[Prey (2019 American film)|Prey]]'' (2019)\n* ''[[Killing Hasselhoff]]'' (2017)\n* ''[[Careful What You Wish For (film)|Careful What You Wish For]]'' (2016)\n* ''[[99 Homes]]'' (2015)\n* ''[[Life of Crime (film)|Life of Crime]]'' (2014)\n* ''[[Ghost Rider: Spirit of Vengeance]]'' (2012)\n* ''[[The Double (2011 film)|The Double]]'' (2011)\n* ''[[Dylan Dog: Dead of Night]]'' (2011)\n* ''Killer'' (2010)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bloody-disgusting.com/news/19233|title=Hyde Park Hunts Latest 'Killer'}}</ref>\n* ''Risen: The Story of the First Easter'' (2009) \n* ''[[Dark Country]]'' (2009)\n* ''[[Street Fighter: The Legend of Chun-Li]]'' (2009)\n* ''[[The Other End of the Line]]'' (2008)\n* ''[[Asylum (2008 film)|Asylum]]'' (2008)\n* ''[[Death Sentence (2007 film)|Death Sentence]]'' (2007)\n* ''[[Premonition (2007 film)|Premonition]]'' (2007)\n* ''[[Raising Helen]]'' (2004)\n* ''[[Walking Tall (2004 film)|Walking Tall]]'' (2004)\n* ''[[Bringing Down the House (film)|Bringing Down the House]]'' (2003)\n* ''[[What's the Worst That Could Happen?]]'' (2001)\n* ''[[Bandits_(2001_film)|Bandits]]'' (2001)\n* ''[[If... Dog... Rabbit...]]'' (1999)\n* ''[[The White Raven (1998 film)|The White Raven]]'' (1998)\n* ''[[A Murder of Crows (film)|A Murder of Crows]]'' (1998)\n* ''[[Billy Frankenstein]]'' (1998)\n* ''[[Black Thunder (film)|Black Thunder]]'' (1998)\n* ''[[Jeans (1998 film)|Jeans]]'' (1998)\n* ''[[Strategic Command (film)|Strategic Command]]'' (1997)\n* ''[[The Shooter (1997 film)|The Shooter]]'' (1997)\n* ''[[Inferno (1997 film)|Inferno]]'' (1997)\n* ''[[Steel Sharks (film) | Steel Sharks]]'' (1997)\n* ''[[Night Hunter (1996 film)|Night Hunter]]'' (1996)\n* ''[[Illicit Dreams]]'' (1994)\n* ''[[Night Eyes 3]]'' (1993)\n* ''Snapdragon'' (1993)\n* ''Tropical Heat'' (1993)\n* ''Sexual Response'' (1992)\n* ''Illicit Behavior'' (1992)\n*'' Night Eyes 2'' (1992)\n* ''[[Double Impact]]'' (1991)\n* ''Eyewitness to Murder'' (1991)\n* ''[[Popcorn (1991 film)|Popcorn]]'' (1991)\n* ''[[Night Eyes]]'' (1990)\n* ''[[Bloodstone (1988 film)|Bloodstone]]'' (1988) (co-producer)\n* ''[[School Spirit]]'' (1985)\n* ''Nine Deaths of the Ninja'' (1985)\n\n===As Executive Producer===\n* ''[[Machete (2010 film)|Machete]]'' (2010)\n* ''[[Traitor (film)|Traitor]]'' (2008)\n* ''Dead of Night'' (2009)\n* ''[[Battle in Seattle]]'' (2007)\n* ''[[Trade (film)|Trade]]'' (2007)\n* ''[[Dreamer (2005 film)|Dreamer]]'' (2005)\n* ''[[Moonlight Mile (film)|Moonlight Mile]]'' (2002)\n* ''[[Original Sin (2001 film)|Original Sin]]'' (2001)\n* ''[[Antitrust (film)|Antitrust]]'' (2001)\n* ''[[Get Carter (2000 film)|Get Carter]]'' (